 sauce into mixing bowl and cook <b>7 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>. Transfer into a bowl. Rinse mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma dish into position and weigh potatoes into it. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>40 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Meanwhile, after meatloaf has cooked for 30 minutes, carefully remove loaf tin from meatloaf and baste with three-quarters of the reserved tomato sauce mixture. Bake for a further 20 minutes (without tin)."},{"content":"Carefully transfer steamed potatoes onto baking tray next to the meatloaf, cover with meat juices, and continue to cook meatloaf for 20-30 minutes, until juices run clear. Serve meatloaf and potatoes with vegetables of choice."}],"hintsAndTricks":["To make your own tomato sauce, please refer to the recipe in <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> or the <i>Everyday Cookbook<\/i>."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 35m","6 portions"]}